This paper deals with information extraction using deep neural networks and transfer learning, which are commonly studied in the fields of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of statistical classifiers, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning models (cs.AI) and the processing of textual data (cs.IR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.CV), which are commonly used in computer vision but can also be applied to NLP tasks.
